        <article class="about-article">
            <h2 class="section-title">The Result: Empathetic Design Through Collaboration</h2>
            
            <p>
                The transformation succeeded. The design system is now unambiguously **Humanist Modernist**: warm, readable, and explicitly designed to serve the human reader rather than express geometric ideals.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="subsection-title">Measurable Outcomes</h3>
            
            <ul class="outcomes-list">
                <li><strong>Typography:</strong> Body text increased from 14px to 18-21px. Line-height increased from 1.4x to 1.7x. All aggressive caps and tracking removed.</li>
                <li><strong>Layout:</strong> Container max-width set to 800px (optimal reading measure). Section padding increased to var(--spacing-2xl) for generous vertical rhythm.</li>
                <li><strong>Visual Softness:</strong> All borders now use 4-6px radius. All shadows reduced to subtle 2-4px elevation. Color palette shifted to warm, muted tones.</li>
                <li><strong>Code Simplicity:</strong> Eliminated 50+ CSS rules related to geometric decoration, pseudo-element animations, and color complexity.</li>
                <li><strong>Philosophical Consistency:</strong> Every remaining design decision serves a clear HM principle. No decorative complexity survives without justification.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 class="subsection-title">The Broader Insight: AI as Empathy Tool</h3>
            
            <p>
                This project demonstrates a profound truth: **AI can be an effective tool for achieving empathetic design goals**. The common assumption is that AI produces cold, generic, or inhumane results. This project proves otherwise—when guided by explicit constraints rooted in human-centered principles, AI can systematically enforce the very philosophy that Humanist Modernism advocates.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                The AI's elimination of geometric ornamentation, hard shadows, and aggressive typography was not a limitation—it was the successful execution of a humanist vision. By removing the layers of complexity that designers often add in the name of "sophistication," the AI revealed the underlying truth of HM: **clarity and warmth are not simplistic; they are the highest form of design sophistication**.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="subsection-title">Why This Matters</h3>
            
            <p>
                In an era of AI-generated design, this project offers a model: **Vibe Coding with metric-driven constraints**. Rather than asking AI to "make it beautiful" or "improve the UX," designers can specify precise, measurable principles rooted in human psychology and accessibility science. The result is not generic—it is deeply human-centered because every constraint serves human comfort and comprehension.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                The transformation from Bauhaus to Humanist Modernism is complete. The design system now embodies a philosophy older than Bauhaus itself: that good design is invisible because it serves the user so completely that the user forgets they are experiencing design. They are simply reading, understanding, and engaging with content.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                <strong>The final insight:</strong> The best collaboration between humans and AI is not about AI learning to design like humans. It is about humans using AI as a tool to enforce the constraints that make design truly human-centered. When design serves the reader instead of the designer, both humans and machines can work toward the same goal: clarity serving humanity.
            </p>
        </article>
